        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="338" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d338">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President’s Special Assistant</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HHL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d338fn1">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_614">p. 614</ref>. This and subsequent <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> notes have been transcribed
                        literally from facsimiles of the handwritten originals.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Yalta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-05">February 5,
                            1945.</date>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. President</hi>:—</p>
                <p>I would suggest that you say this is a very important and urgent matter and that
                    the three foreign ministers present a proposal tomorrow as to the <hi rend="italic">proceedure</hi> by which a determination as to to
                    dismemberment can be arrived at an early date</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
